story.title: Dead Air - Episode 7
story.storyDescription: Halfway through a seven-hour flight to Paris, a woman wakes up to find everyone on the plane is dead except for her…
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Travis Pennington is a writer, literary agent, graphic artist, and leader of a crazy pack of canines. He loves ice cream because it’s cheaper than therapy, and he’s probably the most talented horror binge watcher you’ll ever find.

story.prePaywallNotification: Is Chrissy’s brother on the plane with her?  How can that be?! Read DEAD AIR.
story.postPaywallNotification: How can a man who was DEAD be ALIVE again? Find out by reading the rest of DEAD AIR.

messages.text: What happened with the dead people?
We just got to the airport.
The flight information says your plane is on time.
Take Sylvie and go back to the car.
I’m still on the plane and we’re about to land.
The flight attendant made me go back to my seat for landing.
Didn’t you say everyone was dead?
They WERE dead. But not anymore.
After the lady told me to return to my seat, I went downstairs…
I’m as confused as you are.
Everyone was just fastening their seatbelts.
And what is your brother doing there?
He’s the reason you should stay in your car.
I’d been texting with him for over an hour.
And somehow, he’s been here the entire time.
He’s sitting next to a little boy in first class, holding his hand.
What are you going to do?
As soon as we get to the gate, I’m going to run.
I’m not going to wait for them to let the first-class passengers off first.
I’m going to run off the plane and find security.
That might not be the best idea.
And they almost certainly won’t let you through customs.
But I HAVE to tell someone.
Then we can go to the police together.
I know a cop in Paris.
Just stay in the car with Sylvie.
I’ll text you as soon as I’m through customs.
We’ve been waiting in the car.
Please tell me you’re all right.
I’m in the line at customs.
I was too busy looking for John and that little boy.
I don’t know if that’s good or bad news.
I’m getting out of the car.
Stay in the car with Sylvie.
And I’m not talking about John disappearing after I saw him on the plane.
I just saw a man from the plane.
His wife was texting him during the flight.
And I used his phone on the plane to reply to her, to tell her what was happening.
And now this guy’s texting on his phone…
He was DEAD on the plane.
I need to talk to him.
At least wait until you’re through customs.
No matter what you do, stay away from here!
I asked to borrow his phone…and he held it out.
And just as I was about to take it, he started coughing.
Take Sylvie and get away from the airport.
More passengers from my flight are starting to cough up blood.
Blisters are popping out on their arms.
Like the people in the town I grew up in…
On the day they all died along with my parents.
The man with the phone just coughed up another puddle of blood.
And the customs officers and passengers from other planes…
They’re starting to cough up blood as well.
I’m the only one who isn’t.
I see my brother John and that little boy.
They’re staring at me through the glass of a security door.
And now John just opened the door.
He’s waiting for me to come inside.
